The Romanian water utility Compania
Regionala de Apa Bacau SA awarded a contract valued at 42
million lei ($12 million) to a unit of  Greece â€™s Aktor SA for
engineering design services at a water-treatment plant.  The contract, initially valued at 64.3 million lei, is for
upgrades to the plant in the eastern town of Bacau, according to
a  European Union notice  published today. The utility received
six bids for the contract, the document showed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
